### CHAPTER LXIV.

1\. *As to* the sixty-third question *and* reply, that which you ask is
thus: Whence *was* the first creation of mankind, and how was the
formation of the original race of men? 2. What issued from
Gâyômar*d* <span id="fr_729"></span>[4](#fn_726.md), *and* what did it
really become; and from what have Mashyâîh *and* Mashyâyôîh <span
id="fr_730"></span>[5](#fn_727.md) arisen?

3\. The reply is this, that Aûha*r*ma*zd*, the all

<span id="page_198">p. 198</span>

ruling, produced from the endless light the shape of a fire-priest
(âsrûkŏ) whose name *was* that of Aûha*r*ma*zd*, and *its* brilliance
that of fire; *its* incombustibility was like *that* inside the light,
*and its* expansion like the western (khûrbarag) land. 4. And in the
shape of the fire-priest *was* created by him the material existence
(stih) *that* is called man, *and for* three thousand years <span
id="fr_731"></span>[1](#fn_728.md), when it did not progress and did not
eat, it did not speak; likewise, it did not utter, but it thought of,
the righteousness of the perfect *and* true religion, the desire for the
pure glorification of the creator.

5\. Afterwards, the contentious promise-breaker <span
id="fr_732"></span>[2](#fn_729.md) injured the life of it, *and* produced a
burdensome mortality; and the mortality is *clear* from the appellation,
Gâyômar*d* <span id="fr_733"></span>[3](#fn_730.md), of the nature
produced. 6. The seed which *was* the essence of the life of the leader
(mîrakŏ) of life, who *was* Gâyômar*d*, flowed forth on *his* passing
away, came on to the earth of the beneficent angel <span
id="fr_734"></span>[4](#fn_731.md), *and* is preserved in the earth until,
through the protection of the angels, a brother and

<span id="page_199">p. 199</span>

sister of mankind <span id="fr_735"></span>[1](#fn_732.md), connected
together, have grown from it, *have* attained to movement *and* walking
upon the earth, *and* have advanced even to intercourse and also
procreation.

7\. The ground where the life of Gâyômar*d* departed is gold, *and* from
the other land, where the dissolution of *his* various members occurred,
as many kinds of decorative metals flowed forth it is said <span
id="fr_736"></span>[2](#fn_733.md).

